  "texts": [
    "When evaluating the reconstruction loss, it is assessed relative to layer 1 rather than the input layer.",
    "The encoding process can be mathematically represented as follows:",
    "in which k represents the k-th autoencoder, a k represents the encoding outcome of the k-th autoencoder, and when k = 1, a 0 = x denotes the input data.",
    "The decoding process can be mathematically represented as follows:",
    "when k = 1, c 0 = a n, and when k = n, c n = x represents the reconstructed data of the input variable x (Hoang and Kang 2019)."
  ],
